You are working on Kora — a B2B SaaS platform for high school community service tracking.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- tRPC for API layer, Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL via Supabase
- Clerk for auth (three roles: STUDENT, ORG_MODERATOR, SCHOOL_ADMIN)
- Turborepo monorepo: apps/web, apps/admin, packages/db, packages/ui

## Code Rules
- Always use TypeScript. No `any` types ever.
- Use tRPC procedures for all internal API calls. Never raw fetch to /api routes.
- All DB access goes through `packages/db`. Never import Prisma directly in app code.
- Tailwind only for styling. No inline styles. No CSS modules.
- Server components by default. Add "use client" only when strictly necessary.
- Use Zod for all input validation on tRPC procedures.
- shadcn/ui for all UI primitives. Don't build from scratch what shadcn covers.

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase
- Files: kebab-case
- DB models: match Prisma schema exactly
- tRPC routers: camelCase, grouped by domain (shift, user, org, school)

## Security Rules
- QR tokens are HMAC-signed with a server secret. Never expose raw IDs in QR codes.
- Hours are never self-reported. Always require ORG_MODERATOR verification.
- School admins can only query data scoped to their schoolId — enforce at query level.
- Fraud flagging triggers when 3+ students log identical unverified hours within 10 minutes.

## Model Selection
Use extended thinking / reasoning mode for:
- Designing the QR HMAC token scheme
- Multi-tenant data isolation architecture
- AI matching algorithm design
- Any decision touching security, compliance, or FERPA

Use fast mode for:
- UI components and Tailwind styling
- tRPC boilerplate
- Prisma query writing
- Config and setup tasks

## Agent Skills

Skills live in `.agents/skills/`. **Read the relevant `SKILL.md` before acting** — do not improvise when a skill applies.

### Mandatory workflow

1. **Brainstorming** (superpowers) — use before any creative work: new features, components, behavior changes, or UI work. Present a design and get approval before writing code.
2. **Design skills** (`.agents/skills/`) — use whenever the task touches visual design, UX polish, branding, or frontend aesthetics. If there is even a small chance a design skill applies, read it first and follow it.

### Design skill picker

| Task | Skill |
|---|---|
| New landing page, portfolio, or marketing site | `design-taste-frontend` |
| Redesign or polish existing UI | `redesign-existing-projects` |
| Premium agency-level visual standards | `high-end-visual-design` |
| UI polish, animation, micro-interactions | `emil-design-eng` |
| Minimalist / editorial aesthetic | `minimalist-ui` |
| Brutalist / industrial dashboard aesthetic | `industrial-brutalist-ui` |
| GSAP motion, editorial landing pages | `gpt-taste` |
| Brand identity, logo systems, guidelines | `brandkit` |
| Generate web design reference images | `imagegen-frontend-web` |
| Generate mobile screen concepts | `imagegen-frontend-mobile` |
| Implement from a design image or mockup | `image-to-code` |
| Google Stitch / DESIGN.md design systems | `stitch-design-taste` |
| Large UI output that must not truncate | `full-output-enforcement` |
| Legacy v1 taste-skill behavior only | `design-taste-frontend-v1` |

Default for Kora student/org portal UI work: `redesign-existing-projects` + `emil-design-eng`. Default for new marketing pages: `design-taste-frontend`.
